<TITLE> Ensure neutral probe, not farce: Delwar </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 11 (bdnews24.com)  BNP secretary general Khandaker Delwar Hossain Wednesday asked the government to oversee a fair probe, not a farce, to try the perpetrators of the BDR killings. "Ensure a fast trial of the real criminals after an impartial investigation and don't make a farce for applause from the people," the BNP leader demanded at a condolence meeting organised in the city by Jatiyatabadi Jubo Dal. A condolence rally was brought out after the meeting at the Muktangan. He said comments by the ministers and ruling party leaders were influencing the probe. "It's not fair on the part of the ministers to comment from a standpoint when the investigations are being carried out." Such comments will affect the probe, he said. Delwar added that they wanted to help the government all the way to bring the criminals to justice, but the government was neglecting the opposition. b
